✨ BOOM, SNAP, CLAP ✨ with math operations! 

We premade these math operation cards and put them into ziplock bags. Each set of partners gets a bag and sits across from each other. The sets of partners all line up and form two lines sitting across from each other. One line is a team and the other line is a different team. Their goal is to grab the math operation card before their partner sitting across from them to get a point for their team. Which ever team has the most of the correct card held up, gets the point for the round.

We saw a primary teacher on TikTok do this with letter sounds and wanted to make it work with our 5th graders for math! They absolutely love this game ➗➕✖️➖

Too much labor and money has gone into this classroom but I love how happy and cozy of a space it is for both me and my students 🥺🌈✨ New teachers, this is a reminder to take your time when accumulating/buying things for your classroom. A little space that brings me joy 🌈✨ Let’s be real, we all know that anything in rainbow order brings me joy. My math binders are where I keep original copies of worksheets, lessons, mini anchor charts, etc for each unit. I made the binder spines and covers in PowerPoint. I printed the binder spines onto full page label paper and cut them out so I could just stick them to the outside of the binder! So much easier than trying to shove them down into the plastic of the spine 😂
